{
  "texts": [
    "While the DSA and DMA share complementary aims around ensuring online platform accountability, their scopes differ.",
    "The DSA establishes horizontal rules governing illegal content, platform responsibilities, and algorithmic transparency.",
    "In contrast, the DMA intervenes in platform competition dynamics and economic fairness issues through a set of do's and don'ts that only apply to designated gatekeeper entities meeting specific thresholds.",
    "We define as Digital Single Market the European Union's strategy to ensure the free movement of persons, services and capital in the EU's single market in the digital age.",
    "It aims to open up digital opportunities and provide fair conditions for digital services to flourish in the EU common market, while protecting consumer and personal rights."
  ]
}